og I will show how it can be used to stop & start Azure Firewall in both a schedule and invoking using a webhook. Secondly, if you employ Hybrid Workers for your automation scenarios, you have to manage and update the required PowerShell module by your own means . Another area is Windows Azure Pack / Azure Stack, where he does implementation, development, workshops and presentations. Stellen Sie Windows-Desktops und -Apps mit VMware und Windows Virtual Desktop bereit. Office 365. Azure Automation allows our scripts to run for up to 3 hours vs 10 mins for Azure Functions. 6. Azure is mature enough already that you could do that with other technology. Login to Azure portal with contributor access. Cloud ends Data-center Virtualization ? For each resource deployment, we can pass the standard tags but at some point, it will become painful since we might need to pass the value for more than 10 tags for each resource deployment. Example #1: “On Call Service” Teams Call Queue redirection. For convenience purposes but also for keeping the cost down while you’re not using the Azure VMs. This could be an issue with very long-running provisioning scenarios requiring you to design around the limitation in Azure Functions (“function chaining”, for example) For instance a mix of Scheduler and Web Job. Virtuelle Citrix-Apps und -Desktops für Azure. In this article, we will see how to create a Runbook, which will be used to automate the tasks or implement some logic on behalf of the user.To create a Runbook, go to Azure Automation in Azure portal and click on Runbooks tile. 3. For now, let’s talk about assets and start creating them. TypeDescriptionGraphicalBased on Windows PowerShell that uses a graphical editorGraphical… Azure Automation can be used to Build/Deploy/Configure resources, monitor changes, and automate governance activities Automation tasks can be scheduled, run manually, or triggered from an event or alert Automation accounts support Runbooks which are scripts that 